tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE QuantumOptimization (
    algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255),
    circuit_id INT,
    circuit_name VARCHAR(255),
    optimization_level INT
)

CREATE TABLE quantum_circuits (
  id INT,
  algorithm_id INT,
  circuit_description TEXT,
  gate_count INT,
  is_optimized BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumCircuits (
    circuit_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    circuit_name VARCHAR(255),
    circuit_description TEXT,
    algorithm_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES QuantumAlgorithms(algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE OptimizationRecords (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    circuit_id INT,
    optimization_type VARCHAR(50),
    optimization_result TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (circuit_id) REFERENCES QuantumCircuits(circuit_id)
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumCircuits (
    circuit_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    circuit_name VARCHAR(255),
    qubit_count INT,
    gate_count INT,
    optimization_level INT
)

CREATE TABLE QuantumGateLibrary (
    gate_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    gate_name VARCHAR(100),
    gate_type VARCHAR(50),
    gate_matrix TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE CircuitExecutionLogs (
    log_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    circuit_id UUID REFERENCES QuantumCircuits(circuit_id),
    execution_time FLOAT,
    success BOOLEAN,
    execution_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE AlgorithmOptimizationHistory (
    optimization_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    circuit_id UUID REFERENCES QuantumCircuits(circuit_id),
    optimization_date TIMESTAMP,
    optimization_steps INT,
    execution_time FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE QuantumOptimizerConfig (
    config_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    optimizer_name VARCHAR(100),
    optimization_strategy TEXT,
    max_iterations INT,
    learning_rate FLOAT
)
